HEADWORD: Pseudomorphous
<hw>Pseu`do*mor"phous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>pseydh`s</grk> false + <grk>morfh`</grk> form: cf. F.
<ets>pseudomorphe</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not having the true form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pseudomorphous crystal</b></col>, <cd>a crystal which has
a form that does not result from its own powers of
crystallization.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudonavicella</ent>⟦br⟧
